Fun but a little rushed.
Jun 2024 • Couples
Mixed views. Abdul our guide was great, great sense of humour & saved it. It all seemed a little disorganised. However, that was the general feel of Morocco. We were late being picked up. We just chose quads (I thought) so we had to waste some time at the camp while the others had their camel ride. Quads were superb fun. I have never done it before or had motorbikes as I grew up. But I will be looking to do this again. Because we were last in the dining area we well left worrying if we had been missed. Food was excellent and very nice. Personally I found the entertainment painful and cheesy. Traditional maybe, but a little painful. I just realised there was no belly dancers. Then before we could take a breath we were told we were going. Quads excellent fun the rest was not great. We had done similar in Dubai which was leagues above this. I’m not sure how it all works as there were so many different operators doing the same or similar things. So the idea of the activity yes do it, this actual company I would hope there was better. But I don’t know as this was my only exposure. I think quad 5 star, overall 3 star, but I think our was a little rushed as we had a bit of rain and very windy. So it may have been called to a close early due to weather. So not to damage things I would say 4 star.

Going to Agafay desert was amazing!
Dec 2023 • Family
Going to Agafay desert was amazing! Tip: book your trip at around 15:30, we were lucky that are guide asked us to come earlier. We were picked up close to our Riad (3 min walk). Nice touring bus, great driver! Respect driving in the Rocky desert. Our guide Rachid, very friendly and polite. We were with 16 people. We stopped first at small Argan oil location (maybe 10 minutes). After than to the desert. Food was great, couscous, tajine, dessert and tea. It was enough. Good music show and at the end fire show. Thank you guys. Shokran! Culshi mzien. Cheers, the not a Turkish friend
